        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 7:02PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 702 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Columbia Falls, or 11 miles northeast of Evergreen, moving southwest
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half-inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kalispell, Evergreen, Columbia Falls, Somers, Martin City, Creston,
Hungry Horse, La Salle, and Coram.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 2 between mile markers 117 and 131, and between mile markers
135 and 144.
Highway 93 N between mile markers 102 and 119.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
